<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 5000 9100 9200 9400 9900 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 5000, 5000i, 9000, 9000i - TROUBLESHOOTING - ENGINE OIL TEMPERATURE GAUGE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ENGINE OIL TEMPERATURE GAUGE</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s08207x_16.xml" xrefid="x0820711">ENGINE OIL TEMPERATURE GAUGE</hotlnk>
            for operation description.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If warning lights in left gauge cluster work, fuse F4-A is good.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <table id="t0820731" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Engine Oil Temperature Gauge Circuits</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" align="left" colwidth="1.68in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" align="left" colwidth="1.66in"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Remove harness connector (315) from temperature sender. Measure resistance to ground
                                at sender ground circuit.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Sender gnd. circuit to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; or = 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open in ground circuit, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At temperature sender (315), measure resistance to ground at both sender terminals.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(315), sender term. to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace the temperature sender.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Connect sender signal and ground circuits to gauge tester. Select appropriate setting
                                with KEY ON; note if gauge operates properly. Refer to the
                                <hotlnk document="s08207x_51.xml" xrefid="t082071a">Temperature/ Setting Chart</hotlnk>
                                for expected resistance.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Gauge OK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace the sender.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect connector (423) from gauge cluster. Measure resistance to ground at circuit
                                11-GM.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(423), 11-GM to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60; or = 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 11-GM/ 11-GQ/11-GF between connector (423) and left dash panel
                                ground, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (423) measure voltage between circuit 28A and 11-GM.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(423), 28A and 11-GM.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in 28A from fuse F4-A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At the temperature sender, jumper the sender circuit to ground. At connector (423)
                                measure voltage between circuits 30 and 28A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(423), 28A and 30.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in sender circuit between connector (423) and sender, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance between the cluster "G", "I" and "S" terminals and the respective
                                cluster connector terminals.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>G, I, and S terminals.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60; or = 5 Ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the gauge.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the cluster.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
